quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  14,43,"They run forward with necks outstretched, their heads uplifted, their gaze returning not towards them, and in their hearts, a void"
  14,44,"So warn humanity of the day when the punishment will reach them. Then the wrongdoers will say, “Our Lord, respite us for a short-term. We will answer Your call, and follow the messengers.” “What, had you not sworn before, to no end"
  14,45,"“And you lived in the dwellings of people who wronged their own souls. You were clearly shown how We dealt with them, and We put forth parables for you.”"
  14,46,"Mighty indeed were the plots which they hatched, but their plots were within the Sight of God, even though they were enough to shake the hills"
  14,47,"Never think that God would fail His messengers in His promise, for God is Exalted in Power, the Lord of Retribution"
  14,48,"One day the earth will be changed to a different earth, and so will the heavens, and the people will be brought out before God, the One, the Irresistible"
  14,49,"And you will see those who are corrupt that day, bound together in chains"
  14,50,"Their garments of liquid pitch, and their faces covered with fire"
  14,51,"That God may repay each soul according to what it deserves, and indeed God is swift in calling to account"
  14,52,"Here is a message for humanity. Let them take warning from it, and let them know that He is One God. Let the people of understanding take heed"